Module: ramscsi.sys -- RAM-disk SCSI miniport.  Presents the in-RAM
MBR+FAT16 initrd (PVH boot) as a SCSI disk so scsidisk can surface it
as the boot/system volume.  Ported from the Gary Nebbett NT4 RAM-SCSI
sample; the disk's physical base+size come from the boot loader, which
fills this driver's RAMDCFG data section while staging it (no FAT-BPB
introspection, no hardcoded address).

Builds as a SCSI miniport on top of NT 3.5's scsiport.sys, like vioblk
/ nvme2k.  No hardware, no PCI, no interrupt -- every SRB completes
synchronously in HwStartIo; physical RAM is mapped on demand via
ScsiPortGetDeviceBase.

!ENDIF

MAJORCOMP=ntos
MINORCOMP=dd

TARGETNAME=ramscsi
TARGETPATH=$(BASEDIR)\public\sdk\lib
TARGETTYPE=MINIPORT

INCLUDES=..\..\inc

# scsiport for the SCSI miniport + ScsiPortGetDeviceBase API; ntoskrnl
# for DbgPrint / Rtl{Zero,Copy}Memory.  MINIPORT TARGETTYPE doesn't
# auto-include ntoskrnl (it assumes scsiport wraps everything), but we
# call those ntoskrnl routines directly.
TARGETLIBS=$(BASEDIR)\public\sdk\lib\*\scsiport.lib \
           $(BASEDIR)\public\sdk\lib\*\ntoskrnl.lib \
           $(BASEDIR)\public\sdk\lib\*\hal.lib

SOURCES=ramscsi.c    \
        ramscsi.rc
